      section#c-Subhead
        h2 The <code>.c-Subhead</code> Component
        p.
          Put a <code>.c-Subhead</code> sibling adjacent to a heading to create
          a subheading for a page. This can be thought of as a
          <i>tagline</i> or <i>subtitle</i> for the top-level heading.
        figure
          h1 This is a Page Title
          p.c-Subhead This is a subtitle.
        p.
          Notice the differences between the title and subtitle. The title is in a sans-serif,
          monoweight type, in bold and small caps, which provides a very rigid and blocky look. The dark
          blue color itself contrasts the font and gives the title a cool and calming appearance. In
          great contrast, the subtitle is in a script italic type with a dramatic thick/thin transition,
          which looks fragile and dainty. The warmer color, however, gives it a strong pop.
