      section#c-Document
        h2 The <code>.c-Document</code> Component
        p.
          A <code>.c-Document</code> may take the form of a <code>body &gt; main</code> or
          <code>body &gt;&gt; article</code>. The said document should have a <b>status</b> and be marked up
          with metadata. Read
          <a rel="external" href="https://github.com/chharvey/chharvey.github.io/wiki/Document-Status">my technical report on document status</a>
          for more information.
        p.
          Any Element inside a <code>.c-Document</code> may be marked with classes indicating their status.
          Notice we are separating semantics with presentation: the <code>[data-status]</code> attribute
          is unrelated to an Element&rsquo;s class.
        figure
          article.c-Document This is a <code>c.Document</code>.
            p.c-Document__Draft(data-status="draft")       This is a #[code .c-Document &gt;&gt; p.c-Document__Draft   ]. It may be used on an Element with a status of #[b draft   ] inside a document.
            p.c-Document__Complete(data-status="complete") This is a #[code .c-Document &gt;&gt; p.c-Document__Complete]. It may be used on an Element with a status of #[b complete] inside a document.
            p.c-Document__Released(data-status="released") This is a #[code .c-Document &gt;&gt; p.c-Document__Released]. It may be used on an Element with a status of #[b released] inside a document.
            p.
              This is another paragraph in the document.
              #[span.c-Document__Draft(data-status="draft")       This is a #[code .c-Document &gt;&gt; span.c-Document__Draft   ]. It may be used on an Element with a status of #[b draft   ]] inside a document.
              #[span.c-Document__Complete(data-status="complete") This is a #[code .c-Document &gt;&gt; span.c-Document__Complete]. It may be used on an Element with a status of #[b complete]] inside a document.
              #[span.c-Document__Released(data-status="released") This is a #[code .c-Document &gt;&gt; span.c-Document__Released]. It may be used on an Element with a status of #[b released]] inside a document.
        p.
          A Document is normative by default, but may also have informative (non-essential) Elements.
        figure.
          <article class="c-Document">
            <p class="c-Document__Informative" data-informative="">This is a
              <code>.c-Document &gt;&gt; p.c-Document__Informative</code>.
              It may be used on an Element with the <code>[data-informative]</code> attribute.</p>
            <p>This is another paragraph in the document.
              <span class="c-Document__Informative" data-informative="">This is a
                <code>.c-Document &gt;&gt; span.c-Document__Informative</code>.</span>
              It may be used on an Element with the <code>[data-informative]</code> attribute.</p>
          </article>
